<taxonomicName authority="Ferrarezzi, Barbo and Albuquerque, 2005" authorityName="Ferrarezzi, Barbo and Albuquerque" authorityYear="2005" box="[151,959,725,751]" class="Reptilia" family="Colubridae" genus="Apostolepis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ammodites">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,427,725,751]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Apostolepis ammodites</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Ferrarezzi" box="[434,959,725,751]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" refString="Ferrarezzi, H., Barbo, F. E. &amp; Albuquerque, C. E. (2005) Phylogenetic relationships of a new species of Apostolepis from Brazilian cerrado with notes on the assimilis group (Serpentes: Colubridae: Xenodontinae: Elapomorphini). Papeis Avulsos de Zoologia, 45, 215 - 229. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1590 / S 0031 - 10492005001600001" type="journal article" year="2005">
Ferrarezzi, Barbo and Albuquerque, 
<number box="[900,959,725,751]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" value="2005.0">2005</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
“Cobra-de-ferrão, cobra-rainha”
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1382,725,784]" box="[151,384,759,784]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">(Figs. 13.3 and 26.2)</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1436,831,1037]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
First record in the Caatinga. Recorded only in the state of Bahia, close to contact areas with the Cerrado region, 
<quantity metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.4" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" unit="m" value="440.0">440 m</quantity>
elevation. It is widespread in the northeastern portion of the Cerrado, often on grassland areas on sandy soils (
<bibRefCitation author="Ferrarezzi" box="[158,413,903,928]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" refString="Ferrarezzi, H., Barbo, F. E. &amp; Albuquerque, C. E. (2005) Phylogenetic relationships of a new species of Apostolepis from Brazilian cerrado with notes on the assimilis group (Serpentes: Colubridae: Xenodontinae: Elapomorphini). Papeis Avulsos de Zoologia, 45, 215 - 229. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1590 / S 0031 - 10492005001600001" type="journal article" year="2005">
Ferrarezzi 
<emphasis box="[284,345,903,928]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[355,413,903,928]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" value="2005.0">2005</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) and considered a Cerrado endemic (
<bibRefCitation author="Nogueira" box="[853,1099,903,928]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" refString="Nogueira, C., Colli, G. R., Costa, G. &amp; Machado, R. B. (2010) Diversidade de repteis Squamata e evolucao do conhecimento faunistico no Cerrado. In: Diniz, I. R., Marinho-Filho, J., Machado, R. B. &amp; Cavalcanti, R. B. (Eds.), Cerrado: conhecimento cientifico quantitativo como subsidio para acoes de conservacao. Editora UNB, Brasilia, pp. 333 - 375." type="book chapter" year="2010">
Nogueira 
<emphasis box="[970,1030,903,928]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[1040,1099,904,928]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" value="2010.2011">2010</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 2011). Its occurrence in the Caatinga is probably associated to Cerrado enclaves along the Cerrado-Caatinga contact area in Bahia and Minas Gerais states. It has fossorial and psammophylous habits, is diurnal and nocturnal, and feeds on elongated vertebrates (
<bibRefCitation author="Ferrarezzi" box="[288,534,1012,1037]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" refString="Ferrarezzi, H., Barbo, F. E. &amp; Albuquerque, C. E. (2005) Phylogenetic relationships of a new species of Apostolepis from Brazilian cerrado with notes on the assimilis group (Serpentes: Colubridae: Xenodontinae: Elapomorphini). Papeis Avulsos de Zoologia, 45, 215 - 229. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1590 / S 0031 - 10492005001600001" type="journal article" year="2005">
Ferrarezzi 
<emphasis box="[410,467,1012,1037]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[473,534,1012,1037]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" value="2005.0">2005</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
